deskripsi:
Versi Laporan WA :
Technical Report, 13 June 2022
- After block on pukul 17.58LT, PK-LDJ (B737-800) as ID6594 CGK-SUB STD dan saat teknik walk around ditemukan adanya bekas Birdstrike pada bagian pitot.
Aircraft Technical due to Pitot Birdstrike

PIC: PIERE CONDRO
PAX: C : 12/00/00
          Y : 143/01/02

Reason:
- Aircraft Technical (AOG) due to Pitot Birdstrike

Versi Laporan Surat :
BTK6594 departed from Soekarno Hatta International Airport (WIII) to Juanda International Airport (WARR).
The aircraft landed on Runway 10 at WARR. During the landing roll below 100 knots, IAS Disagree appeared momentarily both on Captain’s and FO’s side. After vacating the runway, IAS Disagree disappeared. The Flight Crew didn't see any bird activity on the runway due to dusk time environment
After parked, the Flight Crew reported to the Engineers, then they found that there was a Birdstrike on Pitot Probe Captain’s side. The engineers decided that the aircraft need to be AOG for further maintenance action.
Upon Landing Runway 10, Birdstrike was encountered between 1000m-1500m of runway. Inspection done by engineer. Aircraft is good.

sumber_informasi: Surat Head of Corporate Safety, Security, Quality & Environment Nomor : Citilink/JKTDVQG/LTR-2055/IV/2023 Perihal Laporan Birdstrike & Bird Activity Hazard
deskripsi:
1. After fully parked at P.8 SUB Airport, there were
bloodstains, meat, and bird wings were discovered in the
nose wheel area and aircraft lights.
2. The engineer on duty was conducted a search and
inspection of the inside of the nose wheel.
3. The engineer suggested that a collision might have
occurred in the air.
4. Technical engineer Fajar reported that the aircraft was in
good condition and no problems were found.
5. The bird debris was deemed cleanable.

Dear @juanda.safety@ap1.co.id

Greetings from Malaysia Airlines Surabaya

 

Through this email, we want to Report of Birdstrike Incident Flight Malaysia Airlines, with detail flight as follows

Date : 27 December 2023

Flight No : MH870

Reg : 9M-MSF

Route : SUB-KUL

STD/ATD : 10.00 LT/09.47 LT

Airborne Time : 09.57 LT

 

The Birdstrike incident occurred when the plane after airborne at Juanda International Airport RWY 10 at around 09.57 LT. At the time, the plane hit a flying bird and hit the right-side window (First Officer Windshield 1R).

After landing at KUL, Engineering inspection was carried out, NIL damage. Birdstrike is a threat to aviation safety that can endanger the safety and security of flight. In some cases, bird collisions with an aircraft result in dents in the aircraft body, or even worse, when they enter the aircraft engine. Birds that are sucked into the turbine engine of an aircraft can cause damage to the entire engine.

Therefore, I request that you, the Safety Department of Juanda International Airport take preventive and mitigation measures regarding this incident and also please provide corrective action.

Please find Attached report from our Pilot for your perusal.

 

This is the report of Birdstrike incident that I convey. I hope that you, the safety department of Juanda International Airport, can pay attention and follow up on this report.

1. On May 20th, 2025 an Airbus A320 registered PK-GLU operated as CTV430 departed from
SUB airport bound for BPN airport.
2. As the aircraft lined up on Runway 28 at SUB Airport.
3. During take-off roll, flight crew approached V1 at approximately 120 knots and flight crew
observed three birds on the centerline that then flew toward the right side, in the
direction of ENG #2.
4. Shortly afterward, flight crew noticed a change in engine noise, accompanied by an
increase in N1 vibration up to 3.7 units.
5. All other engine instruments indicated normal conditions, so flight crew continued the
flight to BPN and landed safely.
6. A PIREP was made to the tower, and operations were informed via frequency 131.95 to
relay the information to the BPN station engineer.
7. Upon arrival, an Engineering inspection revealed two nicked compressor blades and one
torn compressor blade.
8. The Engineer assessed the damage and requested a one-hour delay.
9. Following a detailed examination by Engineer personnel, the aircraft was declared AOG
(Aircraft on Ground)

deskripsi:
QG725
"1. Pada pukul 05.49 WIB Pesawat Citilink Take Off runway 10 ketika kecepatan pesawat diantara 80Kts s/d 100Kts Pilot mendengar suara yang tidak biasa. Pilot menginformasikan bahwa pesawat menghantam burung. Setelah dikonfirmasi, PIC memutuskan langsung dilakukan prosedur Reject Take Off di kecepatan 100Kts dan pesawat berhenti total di rwy intersection N3. 
2. Pada pukul 05.51 Pilot menginformasikan kepada ATC bahwa pswt menabrak burung dan meminta kembali ke Apron. 
3. Pukul 05.53 dilakukan runway Inspection dan ditemukan bangkai Kelelawar pada runway. 
4. Pukul 06.03 Runway Inspection telah selesai dilakukan.
5. ⁠Pukul 06.05 WIB penumpang Disembark, tidak ada korban jiwa ataupun terluka. 
6. Terdapat  kerusakan Total 3 (tiga) buah A/C Fan Bleed No.22,23,24 dent dan 1 main wheel harus diganti.
7. Pesawat dinyatakan  AOG, penumpang diberangkatkan menggunakan pesawat pengganti pada pk. 08.18 wib"
